# Define and Reuse GraphQL Fragments

## Requirements
1. Create a reusable GraphQL fragment for User type containing `id`, `name`, and `email` fields
2. Create another fragment for Post type containing `id`, `title`, `content`, and `author` (nested User)
3. Write two queries that use these fragments:
   - A query to get a single user using the User fragment
   - A query to get posts with nested user data using both fragments
4. Demonstrate fragment reuse across multiple queries

## Example

**Fragment Definition:**
graphql
fragment UserFields on User {
  id
  name
  email
}

fragment PostFields on Post {
  id
  title
  content
  author {
    ...UserFields
  }
}


**Query Usage:**
graphql
query GetUser($id: ID!) {
  user(id: $id) {
    ...UserFields
  }
}

query GetPosts {
  posts {
    ...PostFields
  }
}


**Expected Response for GetPosts:**

{
  "data": {
    "posts": [
      {
        "id": "1",
        "title": "GraphQL Guide",
        "content": "Learn GraphQL basics...",
        "author": {
          "id": "1",
          "name": "Alice Johnson",
          "email": "alice@example.com"
        }
      }
    ]
  }
}


## Edge Cases
- Nested fragments (fragment within fragment)
- Using the same fragment in multiple queries
- Fragments with inline fragments for different types

