Implement cursor-based pagination for GraphQL queries that efficiently handles large datasets. Cursor pagination uses encoded identifiers to mark positions in data without relying on offset, making it ideal for real-time data.

**Requirements:**
- Create a pagination interface with cursor, edges, and pageInfo
- Implement cursor encoding/decoding (base64)
- Support forward (first/after) and backward (last/before) pagination
- Calculate hasNextPage and hasPreviousPage correctly
- Handle edge cases (empty results, single page, requesting more items than available)
- Return consistent cursor format

**Type definitions:**
